===Etymology===
From {{etyl|itc-pro|la}} {{m|itc-pro|*flōs}}, from {{etyl|ine-pro|la}} {{m|ine-pro|*bʰleh₃-||flower, blossom}}, from {{m|ine-pro|*bʰel-||to bloom}}.  Cognates include Ancient Greek {{m|grc|φύλλον}}, Gothic {{term|sc=Goth|𐌱𐌻𐍉𐌼𐌰|lang=got}}, Old English {{m|ang|blōstm}}, {{term|blæd||leaf|lang=ang}} (English {{term|blossom|lang=en}}, {{term|blade|lang=en}}) and Sanskrit {{m|sa|फुलम्}}.

